==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extra-uterine
<hw>Ex`tra-u"ter*ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat. &
Med.)</fld> <def>Outside of the uterus, or womb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Extra-uterine pregnancy</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<cd>a condition of pregnancy in which the fetus is not in the uterus,
but in the Fallopian tube or in the abdominal cavity.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extravagance</ent>⟦br⟧
